## How These Dimensions Combine with the 3 Original Proposals

### Combination 1: "Player + Portrait Control Surface"

> Proposal 1 (Player) + Dimension A (Portrait/Landscape) + Dimension C1 (Mixer Strip)

- **Portrait**: Full control surface — now-playing card, BPM knob, mixer strip, rep/random controls, section navigation. No grid.
- **Landscape**: Grid + slim playback bar at bottom. The phone resting sideways on a music stand = score view.

This is the **"two apps in one phone"** approach. Rotation = mode switch, which is natural and requires zero learning.

### Combination 2: "Dashboard + Compressed View + Loop Selection"

> Proposal 2 (Dashboard) + Dimension D1 (Bird's Eye) + Dimension E1 (Checkboxes)

- Each section card shows a compressed "pattern fingerprint" (colored dots grid)
- Cards have checkboxes in the corner to include/exclude from playback
- Tapping a card zooms into the full detailed grid
- Section cards are the central navigation — everything is on them

### Combination 3: "Toolbar + Adaptive Grid + Tap Tempo"

> Proposal 3 (Toolbar) + Dimension B (Adaptive behavior) + Idea F (Tap Tempo)

- Grid auto-adapts: compressed overview when stopped, follow-playhead when playing
- Bottom drawer peek bar includes a "TAP" button for setting tempo
- Drawer half-open shows BPM + rep + random + section selector
- Drawer full-open reveals mixer + section checkboxes for loop selection

### Combination 4: "Portrait Mixer + Landscape Grid + Track Drawer"

> Dimension A (Portrait/Landscape) + Dimension C3 (Track Drawer) + Dimension E1 (Checkboxes)

- **Portrait**: Dedicated mixer screen with large vertical sliders per track, section checkboxes at top, play controls at bottom
- **Landscape**: Clean grid (no inline volume), tap track name to expand mini-drawer for quick volume adjustment
- Rotating the phone feels like flipping between "mix desk" and "sheet music"

### Combination 5: "The Practice Studio"

> Idea H (Practice Bookmarks) + Dimension B (Adaptive) + Dimension E1 (Checkboxes) + Idea G (Haptic)

A fully practice-oriented redesign:

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ ☰  Agguere 1 - Base          📌 Bookmarks   ▶ │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                │
│   Grid (adaptive: compressed or scrolling)     │
│                                                │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ♩=80 [TAP]  ──●──────    ×4 🎲   CNT ⓸      │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ☑ Base  ☑ Var  ☐ Bridge  ☑ Coda    📳 Haptic │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Bottom area has 2 rows:
1. Tempo + reps + count-in (the practice parameters)
2. Section checkboxes + haptic toggle (the loop configuration)

### Combination 6: "Minimal Player + Power Drawer"

> Proposal 1C (Focus Mode) + Proposal 3A (Quick-access chips) + Dimension A3 (Two-app feeling)

The most minimal of all:
- **Landscape**: Grid + peek bar ("×4 🎲 | ♩=80 | Base 1/3"). Tap chips to tweak values. Double-tap tracks to solo/mute.
- **Portrait**: Full-featured control panel. Large BPM, mixer, sections, bookmarks.
- Zero clutter in landscape. All power in portrait.

